  "prompt": "How can you see if someone deleted you on LINE?",
  "response": "LINE, like many messaging apps, does not provide a direct way to see if someone has deleted or blocked you. However, there are a few indirect signs that might indicate this:\n\n1. **Status and Display Changes**: If you previously could see someone's status updates or profile picture changes and now you can't, it may be a sign that they've deleted or blocked you. However, they might have also changed their privacy settings.\n\n2. **Messaging**: Send a message. If your message is not marked as \"Read\" even after a considerable amount of time, it might mean that they have blocked or deleted you, although they could also just be inactive.\n\n3. **Timeline Posts and Comments**: If you can't see their timeline posts, or if your comments on their posts are no longer visible, they may have changed their privacy settings, deleted you, or blocked you.\n\n4. **Calls**: Try making a call. In some cases, if you are blocked, the call might not connect or might get disconnected immediately.\n\nRemember, these methods are not foolproof. Privacy settings, app glitches, or inactivity could also explain any observations you make.",
